The paper focuses on zero-shot learning using visual features, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of semantic descriptions of classes, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed methods on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
